reviewText: Under the Streetlamp. Great songs, Fantastic choreography. Real memory trip. we love them. bought copy or my sister. Looking forward the 2015 show.

My mother really liked this show, but I couldn't find it on DVD.  After many months I finally found it.  When she received it she complained about how much it cost, but then she said how much she enjoyed it.  Normally I wouldn't pay that much for a DVD.  But for my mother, whatever makes her happy.  And this DVD certainly did.

Excellent performance of old-time favorites.  the best part is that you feel like you're right there at the theater watching it all live ...and you can repeat the experience whenever you choose.  It was well worth the price.
A bit costly but well worth the money.  I love it!
So much better than Jersey Boys.  Fun, Entertaining, You Won't Be Disappointed!
I already knew that i would love it.  I have seen it but wanted to own it.
My husband has played and enjoyed it so many times.  It was music he enjoyed when he was younger.  Their sound and harmony is amazing.
The DVD seems to play just fine, and the service was quick...
Such a wonderfully fun, feel-good concert!!!
Loved every minute of the show.  Would love to see them live!  They are all fantastic
